Database: MS SQL Server

When upgrading Confluence to version 5.3 or later, the 'user_mapping' table should be altered based on the database collation instead of server collation. If the server collation is different than the database collation (e.g: '{{Latin1_General_CI_AS}}' instead of '{{SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CS_AS}}'), the upgrade will fail when trying to access 'user_mapping' table because of conflict in collation.

This is important and would benefit some users if being implemented.

