Currently, if you disable a blueprint via 'Global page blueprints', it instantly disappears in all the space template lists. This means that if you wanted to selectively enable a certain blueprint for only one space in your 100 space instance, you would have to go through and disable it in all 99 other spaces, rather than disabling it globally and then overriding that with an enable in the space you actually want to use it in.

When working on Confluence mobile plugin I noticed a few issues which warrant investigation:

1. Grant Anonymous access in Confluence. Navigate to a page you are not authorized to view. The mobile page, CSS and JS resources will load but when an AJAX call attempts to load the content it will return a 401 causing the application to redirect to the login screen. This is a jarring experience for the user because the page appears to load (not to mention loads a large amount of assets only to redirect the user) The reason is that the Mobile CanUseFilter.java uses the following logic to redirect to the login screen:
{code}
// will always evaluate to false with Anonymous access turned on so user is not
// redirected to login screen even if there is no permission to view the page
if (!permissionManager.hasPermission(remoteUser, Permission.VIEW, PermissionManager.TARGET_APPLICATION))
{
    if (remoteUser == null)
    {
        response.sendRedirect(createLoginUrl(request));
        return;
    }
    else
    {
        response.sendError(403, "Not permitted to use the application.");
        return;
    }
}
{code}

2. If a user is logged in and goes to a page they are not authorized to view they will get a 403 "Not permitted to use the application." when in Confluence on the desktop they will get a 404.

3. If a user restricts a page to themselves and another user attempts to view it, they get a 404 Not Found from the content REST resource where in Desktop Confluence they will get the option to request permission from the administrator.

Scenario #1 is the most bothersome, but it would be nice to address all 3.

