If I have a table that whose bottom row includes a cell that is vertically merged with one or two rows above, I am only able to add new rows within the vertically merged cell. There is no way to add a new row that doesn't keep spanning the vertically merged section. 

Not to solve this but one suggestion is that I can click into the unmerged cell in the final row, and click add row below and it would add a new row that ignores the vertical merge. I could always click on the same cell and add a row above if I want to add additional rows that are within the scope of the vertically merged cells.
